“They told me that if I stayed they would not be responsible for my safety. I knew that meant… they will rape me and discover who I am, then they will kill me.” Shirine is transgender woman from #Syria. Because of her sexuality she has been arrested and spent many months in prison. She escaped with her life in #Syria after receiving death threats from both The Free Syrian Army and her own brother.
